Arsenal welcome Standard Liege in the Europa League Match Day 2. The Gunners kickstarted their quest to win the trophy, with a 3-0 away win at Frankfurt. Liege are joint top with Unai Emery’s men, after also winning 2-0 at home against Vitoria de Guimaraes. Kick of is 8pm West African time. Arsenal XI vs Standard Liege: Martinez, Bellerin, Mustafi, Holding, Tierney, Torreira, Willock, Maitland-Niles, Ceballos, Nelson, Martinelli Thursday, October 3
